Instructions and notices for update script:

The update-dist.php have to be completed with all changes to be made with the system.
It should directly overwrite the config files except /etc/my.cnf and /etc/sudoers.d/oc
(see below). 


##############
# etc-my.cf: #
##############
update is only possible by copying the template per
system('sudo cat [/path/to/etc-my.cnf] > [/etc/my.cnf]')
mysqld does not allow world-writable config-files (they will be ignored)


#####################
# etc-sudoers.d-oc: #
#####################
update is only possible by changing write permissions for /etc/sudoers.d/oc
to allow world edit (i.e. system('sudo chmod 0447 /etc/sudoers.d/oc');), update
the file using the according PHP functions and changing back the permissions (i.e.
system('sudo chmod 0440 /etc/sudoers.d/oc);)

NOT CHANGING BACK THE PERMISSIONS TO '0440' WILL LEAVE THIS SYSTEM UNCONFIGURABLE
VIA THE CONFIG WEBSITE!